“My whole life is dedicated to change.” Sincere- Belly, 1998

S/O to my brother @myname_mikej for extending an invitation. I had the pleasure of covering the @okeebajubalogallery art show and a fashion experience @neimanmarcus back in February, where they featured African American artists and their pieces. I posted highlights back then in my stories (I live there) but, stumbled across the picture in my phone and remembered the line Sincere (@nas) said in the movie Belly. 

Change isn’t always easy, but necessary. From caterpillar to butterfly, #transformationtuesday reminds us of the beauty and power of change. You may not see the results as fast as you’ll like and I know the journey gets rough, but embrace the process and watch yourself soar. Cool? 
#TransformationTuesday #ChangeIsGood #shethoro #prettythoro #art #love #movies

S/O to my videographer @prettythoro 🤞🏾and my sis @avnah for joining me! Follow @myname_mikej and check out his rare collection! #hethoro #shethoro #prettythoro

"Who's Bad" 24x24in. 6 records. I've never made a Mike. My 1st concert ever was Michael Jackson in Cleveland 1980somthing. I remember having a Thriller jacket, wearing one glove, and begging for a curl(didn't happen). Now that I'm older I realize young Mike was the best Mike. 

@motownrecords @classicmotown  @michaeljackson #michaeljackson #kingofpop #motown #motownrecords #vinylgoat #vinylart

Yesterday I took part in my first Jiu-jitsu tournament. It was an amazing experience. I'm proud of myself for even entering. Julia-Rose got cold feet. I really enjoyed having her there. She got to see me win... and she saw me lose. Ultimately I lost in the finals by an armbar. I learned alot, and know exactly what I have to work on. While I'm disappointed I didn't personally win gold, I'm happy that I was able to contribute an overall team Gold for Buckhead Jiu-jitsu. 

Thank you to the @buckheadjj family for the support. I know it may have seemed like I wasn't listening, but I heard u guys, and I really appreciated the guidance. I want to give a special thanks to the 12pm guys...the "lunch crew". Thank u for working with me, and not JUST destroying me(I appreciate both). This medal belongs to u guys as much as me✊🏿

#buckheadjj #bjj #Jiu-jitsu #Naga @nagafighter #atlanta

"Jean-Michel" 24x36in. 12 records on a clear acrylic sheet. This is the second in a set from the Michael Halsband 1985 photo shoot featuring JMB & Andy Warhol. Basquiat executive produced an album for Rammellzee and K-Rob, which features Basquiat's artwork on the cover. That album cover art is featured in this piece.
